comment: Identifier for sleeping stage, as returned by {@link Stage#getType()}.

variables.name: STAGE_TYPE_UNKNOWN
variables.comment: Use this type if the stage of sleep is unknown.

variables.name: STAGE_TYPE_AWAKE
variables.comment:
* The user is awake and either known to be in bed, or it is unknown whether they are in bed
         * or not.

variables.name: STAGE_TYPE_SLEEPING
variables.comment: The user is asleep but the particular stage of sleep (light, deep or REM) is unknown.

variables.name: STAGE_TYPE_AWAKE_OUT_OF_BED
variables.comment: The user is out of bed and assumed to be awake.

variables.name: STAGE_TYPE_SLEEPING_LIGHT
variables.comment: The user is in a light sleep stage.

variables.name: STAGE_TYPE_SLEEPING_DEEP
variables.comment: The user is in a deep sleep stage.

variables.name: STAGE_TYPE_SLEEPING_REM
variables.comment: The user is in a REM sleep stage.

variables.name: STAGE_TYPE_AWAKE_IN_BED
variables.comment: The user is awake and in bed.

variables.name: VALID_TYPES
variables.comment:
* Valid set of values for this IntDef. Update this set when add new type or deprecate
         * existing type.
         *
         * @hide

variables.name: DURATION_EXCLUDE_TYPES
variables.comment:
* Sleep stage types which are excluded from sleep session duration.
         *
         * @hide
